O-On second thought, I'm heading back to Tokyo.

14
00:00:54,340 --> 00:00:59,230
There aren't any trains going to Tokyo this late, are there?

15
00:00:59,230 --> 00:01:01,970
Th-Then I'll go book another room.

16
00:01:01,970 --> 00:01:03,620
This hotel is fully booked tonight.

17
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:06,090
Right.

18
00:01:06,090 --> 00:01:07,730
Mr. Caretaker.

19
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:10,750
What is it?

20
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:13,050
Please stay here for the night.

21
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,630
<i>[Unexpected - Love Story in Maison Ginseiso]</i>

22
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,990
What are you doing?

23
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:48,240
I thought I'd sleep down here.

24
00:01:49,390 --> 00:01:51,590
Just sleep on the bed.

25
00:02:10,650 --> 00:02:12,930
G-Good night.

26
00:02:17,190 --> 00:02:18,960
Good night.

27
00:02:28,150 --> 00:02:29,890
- So...
- Oh...

28
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,900
What is it?

29
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,010
Well...

30
00:02:37,940 --> 00:02:40,030
After you.

31
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:15,420
Let's save this...

32
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:22,400
for when you're certain about your feelings for me.

33
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,900
Okay.

34
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,690
Good night.

35
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:47,370
Good night.

36
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:59,430
Your eyes are bloodshot.

37
00:03:59,430 --> 00:04:01,060
Didn't you get any sleep?

38
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:03,610
N-No, I did...

39
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:10,790
Anyway,

40
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,710
I'll see you at the boardinghouse.

41
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:23,010
Take care, okay?

42
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,450
Hello? Tomo-chan?

43
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:37,680
So,

44
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:42,050
you couldn't have ex-wife-approved sex with Shitara Kouichi.

45
00:04:42,050 --> 00:04:45,000
I was so on edge all night!

46
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,120
My discipline was seriously being tested.

47
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:48,680
My condolences.

48
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,890
I mean, can you believe him?

49
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:54,800
He came all the way from Tokyo and even kissed me!

50
00:04:54,800 --> 00:05:00,460
But a man who isn't easily seduced is a man who doesn't give in to the flow, you know?

51
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:04,330
If anything, that makes him more trustworthy.

52
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,450
Fair point.

53
00:05:06,450 --> 00:05:08,800
<i>Itsuka, set your heart straight</i>

54
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,950
and just confess, okay?

55
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:12,570
<i>[Michiko]</i>

56
00:05:13,210 --> 00:05:15,820
<i>I like our caretaker.</i>

57
00:05:15,820 --> 00:05:17,390
<i>And yet...</i>

58
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,900
<i>You know what?</i>

59
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:26,440
<i>I did a great job holding back, given the situation.</i>

60
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,000
<i>Sure, I couldn't sleep a wink.</i>

61
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,710
<i>But I want to give myself a solid pat on the back.</i>

62
00:05:31,710 --> 00:05:33,970
<i>I did a good job.</i>

63
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:40,690
I'm home.

64
00:05:43,420 --> 00:05:45,290
Oh, Kou-chan,

65
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,860
you spent the night out?

66
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:52,640
I'm sorry. I-I'll get cooking.

67
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,210
Breakfast is already served.

68
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:57,240
<i>I sure hope it suits your taste.</i>

69
00:05:59,410 --> 00:06:00,900
Please, dig in.

70
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:03,070
I've made plenty of seconds.

71
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,020
This is delicious!

72
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:05,070
Really?

73
00:06:05,070 --> 00:06:06,960
That makes me really happy.

74
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:09,850
Oh, Shitara!

75
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:12,110
Tsuchiya, what are you doing here?

76
00:06:12,110 --> 00:06:13,400
You see...

77
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,740
He will be staying for the day while his new apartment

78
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:18,370
is undergoing leakage repairs.

79
00:06:18,370 --> 00:06:21,320
Exactly! You explain my predicament better than I ever could.

80
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,350
Thank you kindly.

81
00:06:22,350 --> 00:06:24,630
Still, why our boardinghouse?

82
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:27,960
Because Tsucchii is a regular of mine.

83
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:31,920
Anyway, I'll be in your care.

84
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,590
Nao-san, please dig in. I've made plenty of seconds.

85
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:36,000
- Thank you.
- Of course.

86
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,230
<i>[Maison Ginseiso]</i>

87
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,630
<i>Tomorrow evening?</i>

88
00:06:39,450 --> 00:06:40,940
Yes, I'm free.

89
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:42,170
In that case,

90
00:06:42,990 --> 00:06:44,860
let's go eat out.

91
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:48,790
A night out with all the tenants?

92
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:51,050
- Great idea.
- No, well...

93
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:59,130
I meant just the two of us.

94
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,100
What?

95
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:05,400
We're going on a date.

96
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:08,430
<i>The bath is now available!</i>

97
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:10,770
Who is this?

98
00:07:10,770 --> 00:07:11,770
And who is this?

99
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:13,820
Nice to meet you.

100
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:17,080
I'm his ex-coworker. I am Tsucchii, or Tsuchiya.

101
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,710
Right?

102
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:20,540
I'll text you once I've booked the restaurant, okay?

103
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,610
There's no need to ignore me.

104
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:31,550
<i>Whenever I'm with our caretaker,</i>

105
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:33,810
<i>I feel the urge to approach him</i>

106
00:07:33,810 --> 00:07:35,980
<i>and touch him.</i>

107
00:07:35,980 --> 00:07:41,420
<i>Honestly, I'd love to confess sooner rather than later.</i>

108
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:43,130
<i>But...</i>

109
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:46,790
<i>Shitara Kouichi isn't the one you can't forgive.</i>

110
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:51,690
<i>You're angry at the part of yourself</i>

111
00:07:51,690 --> 00:07:53,770
<i>that can't forgive Shitara Kouichi.</i>

112
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:00,650
<i>[Chinatown]</i>

113
00:08:18,350 --> 00:08:20,250
Sorry for the wait.

114
00:08:25,090 --> 00:08:27,180
What are you ordering?

115
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:30,320
The mayonnaise shrimp,

116
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,440
fluffy crab and eggs,

117
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,640
mapo tofu,

118
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:36,560
shark fin soup, and pork fried rice.

119
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:38,370
Let's see, what else...

120
00:08:38,370 --> 00:08:41,200
I know, would you like some dumplings?

121
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,300
"Dumplings"?

122
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,520
I think I'll pass.

123
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,640
Still, can you finish all that?

124
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:53,370
No need to worry; I'll pay for my share.

125
00:08:53,370 --> 00:08:54,340
Pardon?

126
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:56,700
Of course not. I invited you out, so it's my treat.

127
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,480
Your job doesn't pay. I'm sure you're short on money.

128
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:02,510
I have enough to treat you.

129
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:05,570
And I don't want you to assert dominance.

130
00:09:05,570 --> 00:09:06,680
What?

131
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:10,150
I wasn't trying to assert...

132
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:16,220
<i>Oh, no!</i>

133
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:18,350
Is something the matter?

134
00:09:18,350 --> 00:09:19,520
We're leaving.

135
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,450
What?

136
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:23,370
- But we haven't even ordered-
- We'll just eat elsewhere.

137
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:25,210
H-H-Hey!

138
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:28,030
Wait, my bag! My bag!

139
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:33,180
Kou-chan?

140
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:35,980
What are you doing?

141
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:40,920
L-Long time no see.

142
00:09:44,610 --> 00:09:46,400
Nice to meet you.

143
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:48,620
I am Kouichi's mother.

144
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:49,770
Pardon?

145
00:09:59,090 --> 00:10:01,110
You're saying you got a divorce

146
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,790
and quit your job?

147
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:06,050
Please explain exactly what's going on.

148
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:11,410
It was Natsumi who asked for a divorce,

149
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:14,920
but it was ultimately my fault for focusing on work

150
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:18,000
instead of our marriage.

151
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,100
When did you quit?

152
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,810
Three months ago.

153
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:24,510
And why did you resign?

154
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:29,960
Because I was going to be fired. It was an impulsive decision.

155
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,700
"An impulsive decision"?

156
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:37,290
What is your current profession?

157
00:10:37,290 --> 00:10:42,330
I am the caretaker of a boardinghouse that Sister Nao introduced me to.

158
00:10:43,470 --> 00:10:45,940
"A boardinghouse"?

159
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:48,600
This person is one of our residents.

160
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:56,790
How much do you earn as caretaker?

161
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,060
I have no salary.

162
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,650
So now you are both divorced

163
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,710
and unemployed.

164
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,340
CEO,

165
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:19,210
I apologize for interrupting. Your next appointment awaits.

166
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:23,020
We shall speak about this case at a later time.

167
00:11:30,860 --> 00:11:32,440
What is it?

168
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:35,490
When life tires you,

169
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:41,010
it is natural to take the easy way out.

170
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:43,040
However,

171
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:48,360
as a result, you will lose your place.

172
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:03,690
To think our caretaker hailed from the infamous Shitara Group

173
00:12:03,690 --> 00:12:08,660
and was the son of "Mommy Shima," the dumpling innovator herself.

174
00:12:08,660 --> 00:12:09,740
Yes,

175
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:11,900
I was shocked.

176
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:16,200
Our caretaker's mother is a single mom

177
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,040
who stands at the top of all successful businesswomen.

178
00:12:20,190 --> 00:12:23,880
I've seen that story on TV before.

179
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:28,280
Her son is equally high-achieving and only works here to make ends meet,

180
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:31,490
seeing as it is both temporary and unpaid.

181
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:33,820
I wonder if he will eventually leave this boardinghouse

182
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:37,000
and quit as caretaker altogether.

183
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,950
<i>As a result,</i>

184
00:12:50,950 --> 00:12:54,890
<i>you will lose your place.</i>

185
00:12:54,890 --> 00:12:58,970
<i>She always hits me right where it hurts.</i>

186
00:13:09,450 --> 00:13:12,560
<i>[Please visit our office at 4 p.m. tomorrow. If possible, we'd like an hour of your time.]</i>

187
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:27,120
Pardon me.

188
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:29,860
Right this way.

189
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,780
Mother.

190
00:13:39,780 --> 00:13:42,330
Please have seat.

191
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:51,610
Allow me to be frank.

192
00:13:51,610 --> 00:13:53,260
Shitara Kouichi-san,

193
00:13:54,710 --> 00:14:00,340
the Shitara Group would like to hire you.

194
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:01,860
What?

195
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:07,080
This document explains our conditions of employment.

196
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,760
The terms should be in your favor.

197
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,580
<i>[Conditions of Employment]</i>

198
00:14:10,580 --> 00:14:13,520
Mother, what sort of joke is this?

199
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:17,210
Entering my parent's company at my age?

200
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:19,040
I'll keep relying on myself-

201
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:22,400
The public eye is ever so strict

202
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,570
toward those who will succeed their parents.

203
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:28,810
I'm sure you are well aware of this.

204
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:34,480
Simply put, you are attempting to escape reality.

205
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,710
I'm not "escaping" from anything.

206
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,860
I just have other work to do.

207
00:14:38,860 --> 00:14:42,020
- Like aiding your residents as caretaker?
- Exactly.

208
00:14:42,020 --> 00:14:44,230
Despite the lack of salary?

209
00:14:44,230 --> 00:14:45,330
Yes.

210
00:14:45,330 --> 00:14:49,500
Then why did you not take pride in your profession

211
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:52,610
and tell me you were working as a caretaker?

212
00:14:53,950 --> 00:14:57,930
Despite being in your prime, you are not working

213
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,790
nor earning a living.

214
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:05,860
You, more than anyone else, must be most dissatisfied with yourself, right?

215
00:15:08,510 --> 00:15:10,740
We, the Shitara Group,

216
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:15,080
soon plan to branch out into the overseas market.

217
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:17,480
Thus, as our pioneer,

218
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:22,690
I'd like to leave the Shanghai branch to you.

219
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:24,940
Sh-Shanghai?

220
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:28,820
Entrust yourself to a challenge

221
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:31,970
and rebuild your career.

222
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:42,790
<i>Let's save this for when you're certain about your feelings for me.</i>

223
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:44,750
<i>Why?</i>

224
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:50,890
<i>Why can't I take the plunge when he gives me the choice?</i>

225
00:15:50,890 --> 00:15:52,810
Nishijima,

226
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:57,240
is work giving you trouble?

227
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,810
No, not really.

228
00:15:59,810 --> 00:16:01,540
Thanks.

229
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:04,470
Then...

230
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,760
is this about Shitara-san?

231
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,170
What?

232
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:15,070
He wants you to be certain, right?

233
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:19,420
In that case, how do you feel?

234
00:16:22,010 --> 00:16:27,170
Well, I want to approach him,

235
00:16:27,170 --> 00:16:30,240
but I end up getting competitive and defensive.

236
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:37,660
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't still bothered by the past.

237
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:42,580
I know things can't remain as they are.

238
00:16:42,580 --> 00:16:43,880
And yet...

239
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:47,580
Nishijima,

240
00:16:48,740 --> 00:16:51,160
you're just protecting yourself

241
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,230
because you don't want to get hurt.

242
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:54,800
What?

243
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,880
That's why you want to avoid

244
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,330
falling in love with Shitara-san.

245
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:03,050
That's how I see it.

246
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,180
You're always honest.

247
00:17:17,580 --> 00:17:21,750
That sincerity of yours is exactly what captured my heart.

248
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:27,500
So answer me honestly.

249
00:17:28,530 --> 00:17:33,800
Do you want Shitara-san to leave you?

250
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:41,740
I think... that's a "no."

251
00:17:41,740 --> 00:17:46,390
What if he suddenly told you, "This is goodbye"?

252
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:52,360
I'd feel... really lonely.

253
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:54,440
Then don't be afraid.

254
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,470
You have to convey your feelings

255
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:04,810
to someone you want at your side.

256
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:15,740
Thank you, Katori.

257
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,090
Such wonderful words of encouragement.

258
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:35,530
No piece of fiction can compare.

259
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,740
Do you want to join me at Dolce?

260
00:18:44,430 --> 00:18:47,560
<i>I was terrified of admitting my feelings for him.</i>

261
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,540
<i>I wanted the leeway of an escape route</i>

262
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:55,940
<i>so I could turn back when necessary.</i>

263
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:59,050
<i>Nishijima Itsuka, I like you.</i>

264
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:02,080
<i>But I'll give it a go.</i>

265
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,450
<i>I don't care if I get hurt.</i>

266
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:08,780
